                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experimental",
                "method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Computer data analysis of proton backscattering from",
                "light elements has been studied."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties in the cross section data results",
                "statistical errors and background subtraction for",
                "sulfur.  In the case of mg, the inaccuracies due to",
                "possible errors in the proton and alpha particle",
                "stopping powers which are used in determining the",
                "relative backscatterig yields of mg and Au, also affect",
                "the cross section data.Consequently, except for the",
                "narrow resonances, the estimated standard error of the",
                "cross section data for sulfur is reduced from 3% to",
                "1.5% as the energy increases.  The uncertainty for mg",
                "falls below 5%.  It should be noted that the",
                "experimental data agree with the rutherford cross",
                "section curves within 1.5% for Mg below 800-KeV and for",
                "sulfur below 1600-KeV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The proton energy is calibrated with an",
                " accuracy of +-3-KeV."
              ]
            }
